DIGEST
SB 247 Original 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Present law (R.S. 46:1602) authorizes a parish voluntary council on the aging to receive
public funds from any governmental or political subdivision upon issuance of charter by the
secretary of state. Such funds are subject to audit by the legislative auditor or his duly
authorized representative.
Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law requires each parish voluntary council on the aging to submit bank statements
to the legislative auditor on a monthly basis. The deadline to submit bank statements shall
be on the last day of each month.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 46:1602(A)(3))
